s of beauty. Vulgar beauty, then, becomes the taste of difference. By demonstrating how Chinese feminine beauty becomes a cinematic invention invested in forms of affective racialization, Zuo makes a critical reconsideration of aesthetic theory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aActresseszChina. 0aAsian American women in motion pictures. 0aFeminine beauty (Aesthetics) in motion pictures. 0aFeminine beauty (Aesthetics)zChina. 0aMotion picture actors and actresseszChina. 0aMotion pictureszUnited States. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022718zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022718423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022718/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles